item.title: By: jeffreyp
item.dc:creator: jeffreyp
item.description:
That's nothing. My pathetic <a href="http://www.jeffreypratt.org/jeffrey" rel="nofollow">website</a> only gets a few dozen hits per month that originate from IPs other than mine. You'll note that said website contains about five static HTML pages, so I'm pretty confident that I know all of the content. And yet, the top search string I get every month, which is not mentioned anywhere on my site: "lego porn".
I couldn't make something like that up even if I wanted to.
